Quote: CAESIOPERCA LEPIDOPTERA (Forster).</i> Red Perch </i>. Called `red snapper' or `St. Peter's fish' in Queen Charlotte and Pelorus Sounds, where it is occasionally taken in the seine net during July and August. ... Distribution* North island coasts and northern coasts of the South Island.
